---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="Features Guide" description="A complete walkthrough of every Ravenburst feature.">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold text-rb-text mb-2">Features Guide</h1>
  <p class="text-rb-muted mb-10">A walkthrough of every major feature in Ravenburst.</p>

  <div class="space-y-12 text-sm text-rb-muted leading-relaxed">

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">The Editor</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Ravenburst uses a full rich-text editor with a two-row format bar above it. The format bar controls character formatting (bold, italic, font, size, colour, highlight) in the top row, and paragraph formatting (alignment, lists, indent, line spacing, tables) in the bottom row.</p>
      <p class="mb-3">Notable editor behaviours:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">No autocorrect.</strong> Ever. What you type is what stays.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">No autocomplete.</strong> No AI whispering sentence completions.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Typewriter mode</strong> — toggle via View menu or Ctrl+Shift+T. Keeps your cursor centred vertically as you type.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Zoom</strong> — scale the editor text independently of your OS zoom. The percentage shows in the status bar.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Navigator & Project Structure</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">The Navigator on the left shows your full project tree. Every project contains:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside mb-3">
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Manuscript</strong> — Parts, Chapters, Scenes in any nesting</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Front Matter</strong> — title page, dedication, epigraph, etc.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Characters</strong> — character cards with full profile fields</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Places</strong> — location cards</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Reference</strong> — notes and images for research</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Notes</strong> — freeform notes not tied to the manuscript</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Templates</strong> — reusable document templates</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">AI Reports</strong> — saved outputs from AI analysis</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Trash</strong> — soft-deleted documents, restorable at any time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Drag to reorder. Double-click to rename. Right-click for context menu options.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Snapshots</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Press <strong class="text-rb-text">Ctrl+Shift+S</strong> at any time to save a named snapshot of the current document. Snapshots are stored permanently — nothing is ever auto-deleted.</p>
      <p>Browse, preview, and restore snapshots from the Snapshots panel (accessible from the document's right-click menu or the Inspector panel).</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Find & Replace</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Ctrl+F</strong> — find within the current document. Supports regex.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Ctrl+Shift+F</strong> — project-wide search across all documents.</li>
        <li>Replace single or all instances. Click a result to jump to the document and highlight the match.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Spellcheck & Dictionary</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Spellcheck runs as you type. Misspelled words are underlined in red. Right-click for suggestions, to ignore, or to add to your custom dictionary.</p>
      <p>Your custom dictionary is stored locally — character names and technical terms you add are remembered between sessions. Manage your dictionary via <strong class="text-rb-text">Edit → Manage Custom Dictionary</strong>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Word Count</h2>
      <p>Word counts appear in the status bar at all times — per document and per project. Select text to see a selection count. Open <strong class="text-rb-text">View → Word Count Panel</strong> for a full breakdown by chapter.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Writing Targets & Statistics</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Set a manuscript word count goal and a daily session target via <strong class="text-rb-text">Project → Project Targets</strong> (Ctrl+Shift+T). Progress bars fill as you write; the session counter resets automatically at midnight.</p>
      <p class="mb-3"><strong class="text-rb-text">Project → Statistics</strong> shows a full breakdown: words, characters, paragraphs, sentences, average lengths, estimated pages, reading time, and word frequency. Switch between compiled-only and all-documents counts.</p>
      <p><strong class="text-rb-text">Project → Writing History</strong> logs your daily word count with a bar chart and streak counter. History accumulates automatically — nothing to configure.</p>
      <p class="mt-2"><a href="/docs/writing-targets" class="text-rb-accent">Full guide →</a></p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Text Cleanup</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Under <strong class="text-rb-text">Edit → Text Cleanup</strong> are four automated cleanup operations for the current document:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Replace Multiple Spaces with Single Space</strong> — collapses any run of spaces into one</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Remove Empty Lines Between Paragraphs</strong> — deletes blank paragraph nodes</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Strip Leading Tabs</strong> — removes tab characters at the start of paragraphs</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Delete Struck-Through Text</strong> — permanently removes any text you've marked with strikethrough</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Line Numbers</h2>
      <p>Toggle paragraph numbers in the editor margin via <strong class="text-rb-text">View → Show/Hide → Line Numbers</strong>. Each paragraph gets a counter in the left margin — useful for script work, proofreading, or workshops where participants need to reference line numbers.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Favorite Projects</h2>
      <p>Add the current project to your favorites with <strong class="text-rb-text">File → Add to Favorites</strong>. Favorites appear in the <strong class="text-rb-text">File → Favorite Projects</strong> submenu for quick access across sessions.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Import</h2>
      <p>Go to <strong class="text-rb-text">File → Import</strong> to import:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside mt-2">
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">.docx</strong> — Microsoft Word (formatting preserved)</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">.txt</strong> — Plain text</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">.md</strong> — Markdown</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">.fountain</strong> — Fountain screenplay format</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">AI Features</h2>
      <div class="bg-rb-surface border border-rb-accent/30 rounded-lg p-4 mb-4 text-rb-muted">
        <strong class="text-rb-text">The AI does not write for you.</strong> Every AI feature is editorial — it finds problems, asks questions, and surfaces information. It will never generate prose, suggest sentences, or complete your thoughts.
      </div>
      <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc list-inside">
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Continuity Check</strong> — scans your manuscript for character inconsistencies, timeline errors, and name variants. Results saved to AI Reports.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Writing Coach</strong> — structural feedback in the form of questions, not rewrites. Challenges your thinking without touching your words.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Reference Assistant</strong> — factual background research. Answers saved to your Reference section, never auto-inserted into your manuscript.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-rb-text">Story Bible</strong> — extracts characters, locations, and events from your chapters automatically.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

  </div>
</DocsLayout>
